power in having that hit game.

00:06:30.674 --> 00:06:32.590
In the case of Supercell,
they didn't break it

00:06:32.590 --> 00:06:34.923
out in terms of the competition
between their two games,

00:06:34.923 --> 00:06:37.465
but virtually all the revenue,
they have a third one coming.

00:06:37.465 --> 00:06:40.090
But virtually, all their revenue
is coming from just two games.

00:06:40.090 --> 00:06:42.200
And so that's clearly
something we're

00:06:42.200 --> 00:06:43.300
seeing as a best practice.

00:06:43.300 --> 00:06:45.216
There was a time when
developers are launching

00:06:45.216 --> 00:06:47.720
a bunch, a bunch of games, but
what we're seeing right now

00:06:47.720 --> 00:06:50.196
is the message to take from
the folks leading the top,

00:06:50.196 --> 00:06:51.695
and their doing
some amazing things,

00:06:51.695 --> 00:06:54.540
but focus is clearly
what's a big part of what's

00:06:54.540 --> 00:06:57.550
winning for these guys.

00:06:57.550 --> 00:06:59.340
In terms of the
larger developers,

00:06:59.340 --> 00:07:00.798
one of the trends
that we're seeing

00:07:00.798 --> 00:07:02.540
is they're adapting
to free-to-play.

00:07:02.540 --> 00:07:07.650
They're amazing game developers,
but free-to-play is definitely

00:07:07.650 --> 00:07:09.010
an art.

00:07:09.010 --> 00:07:11.982
There's a lot of folks out there
that love free-to-play games.

00:07:11.982 --> 00:07:13.440
There's other folks
there that feel

00:07:13.440 --> 00:07:15.030
passionately the other way.

00:07:15.030 --> 00:07:16.994
And so it's something
where you definitely

00:07:16.994 --> 00:07:18.785
need to make sure that
you're doing it well

00:07:18.785 --> 00:07:20.050
and you're doing it right.

00:07:20.050 --> 00:07:22.050
And so to talk a little
bit more about Gameloft,

00:07:22.050 --> 00:07:24.570
so they did a really
interesting experiment last year

00:07:24.570 --> 00:07:27.950
where we worked very closely
with them for Asphalt 8.

00:07:27.950 --> 00:07:31.710
They actually launched that
game in August of last year

00:07:31.710 --> 00:07:34.840
as a premium game
with an app purchase.

00:07:34.840 --> 00:07:38.074
But they had an
explicit experiment,

00:07:38.074 --> 00:07:40.490
which was very cool, to see
how much money they could make

00:07:40.490 --> 00:07:42.700
through in-app
purchase, and could they

00:07:42.700 --> 00:07:44.670
make that game free-to-play.

00:07:44.670 --> 00:07:46.480
And so there they
gave themselves

00:07:46.480 --> 00:07:49.270
a couple of months to
develop the economy there,

00:07:49.270 --> 00:07:53.430
and they found now the
game is free-to-play,

00:07:53.430 --> 00:07:54.930
but the testing
that they did before

00:07:54.930 --> 00:07:58.450
that in the month up to when
they pushed it free-to-play,

00:07:58.450 --> 00:08:01.830
they were making nearly
3/4 of their revenue

00:08:01.830 --> 00:08:05.480
through in-app purchase,
which was really powerful.

00:08:05.480 --> 00:08:07.170
So it went free in
November last year.

00:08:07.170 --> 00:08:08.760
They actually
increased their revenue

00:08:08.760 --> 00:08:13.270
by going free-to-play because
they had built up the economy,

00:08:13.270 --> 00:08:17.110
and then they did 24x their
installs in the 30 days

00:08:17.110 --> 00:08:18.890
post the switch versus pre.

00:08:18.890 --> 00:08:21.130
So it just really speaks
to revenues of piece,

00:08:21.130 --> 00:08:22.810
but just the
engagement they benefit

00:08:22.810 --> 00:08:24.830
from doing this is massive.

00:08:24.830 --> 00:08:27.290
And so it was certainly
a success for them,

00:08:27.290 --> 00:08:29.810
and it feels like
Gameloft is definitely

00:08:29.810 --> 00:08:31.379
developing in shops
in terms of being

00:08:31.379 --> 00:08:32.670
a great free-to-play developer.

00:08:34.940 --> 00:08:36.440
Next big company
is Electronic Arts,

00:08:36.440 --> 00:08:40.520
so their "Simpsons" has clearly
been the big win for them.

00:08:40.520 --> 00:08:43.320
So in terms of just focus and
learning from those larger

00:08:43.320 --> 00:08:45.520
developers,
"Simpsons" has clearly

00:08:45.520 --> 00:08:47.360
been the breakout
success for EA.

00:08:47.360 --> 00:08:51.610
It's been hanging on the top 10,
top grossing for a year plus,

00:08:51.610 --> 00:08:54.290
and so that's just a really
impressive accomplishment.

00:08:54.290 --> 00:08:56.970
When we think about
EA, just great brands

00:08:56.970 --> 00:08:58.510
are just a core
part of the company.

00:08:58.510 --> 00:09:01.810
And so we're really excited to
be working more closely with EA

00:09:01.810 --> 00:09:04.220
to bring-- all of these
brands are there right now.

00:09:04.220 --> 00:09:06.860
